===Verb===
{{en-verb|speaks|speaking|'''[[spoke]]''' ''or archaic'', '''[[spake]]'''|spoken}}

# {{intransitive}} To [[communicate]] with one's [[voice]], to [[say]] [[word]]s [[out loud]].
#: ''I was so surprised I couldn't '''speak'''.''
#: ''You're '''speaking''' too fast.''
# {{intransitive}} To have a [[conversation]].
#: ''It's been ages since we've '''spoken'''.''
# {{context|by extension}} To [[communicate]] or [[converse]] by some other means, such as writing or facial expressions.
#: ''He '''spoke''' of it in his diary''
#: '' '''Speak''' to me only with your eyes.''
#: ''I just '''spoke''' with them on IRC.''
#: ''Actions '''speak''' louder than words''.
# {{intransitive}} To deliver a message to a group; to deliver a [[speech]].
# {{transitive}} To be able to communicate in a [[language]].
#: ''He '''speaks''' Klingon fluently''.

